{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a23672b7-9d95-4ca7-b341-9f08e0b24b5a","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — ❌ Not supported (EOL Dec 2022)\n- **`net5.0`** — ❌ Not supported (EOL May 2022)\n- **`net462`** — ✅ Still supported (.NET Framework 4.6.2+)\n\nMSTest v3 only supports **.NET Framework 4.6.2+** and **.NET 6.0+** (current LTS/STS releases).\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your target frameworks to supported versions, e.g.:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\n**Other MSTest v3 changes to be aware of:**\n- You can consolidate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` into a single **`MSTest`** meta-package.\n- Some APIs have breaking changes (e.g., assertion messages, test lifecycle attributes).\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"05331f5d-6a45-429f-80b9-87f059e14914","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes:\n\n1. **Framework support**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `.NET 5.0` is no longer supported (it's out of support from Microsoft anyway)\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` is no longer supported\n   - `.NET Framework 4.6.2` (`net462`) — MSTest v3 requires .NET Framework 4.6.2 or later, so `net462` should still be supported.\n   - MSTest v3 supports .NET 6.0+ and .NET 8.0+, but the exact supported target frameworks depend on the specific version.\n\n2. **Package consolidation**: MSTest v3 simplifies the package structure by offering a single `MSTest` meta-package instead of requiring separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages.\n\n3. **Compatibility blockers for this project**:\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` is incompatible — it's been out of support since December 2022\n   - `net5.0` is incompatible — it reached end of life in May 2022\n   - `net462` should work fine with MSTest v3\n\nThe user will need to either upgrade their target frameworks to `net6.0` or `net8.0` to use MSTest v3, or stick with MSTest v2 for the older frameworks. There are also breaking API changes in v3 to consider, but the framework compatibility is the main issue here.","outputTokens":820,"requestId":"702B:3BA9A2:3C0490:46B03E:69F2BFF6"},"id":"543b199c-0ec1-4d51-bfff-82ed85016886","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:35:52.120Z","parentId":"0b3fb4ea-1968-4ccd-960d-af49f5d95872"}
